            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "An unexpected benefit of this refactoring is the discovery that this test is likely incorrect. LSP ranges typically represent a single line using `(line, 0)` and `(line + 1, 0)`, rather than `(line, 0)` and `(line, line_count)`. Refactoring this legacy logic using `vim.Pos`/`vim.Range` should help us identify these edge cases and unify their handling in a single place. Ref: https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#range",
            "commit_id": "ff43f1950e1fd3b5ae37924bc8f9c6c3e9d54908",
            "created_at": "2026-05-17T09:45:07Z",
